pageContext.claim: “And the [only primary candidate that he endorsed that] I didn’t get was Friess, I was asked to do that, by my son Don, and I did it but I did it — I was asked the morning of — and by the time I did it I guess 70 percent, almost 70 percent of the vote was already cast. So, I don’t consider that to be, maybe I’ll take a quarter of a loss on that one. But I think it’s 48 and a quarter, it’s 48-1 which is pretty good, right? Pretty good.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is exaggerating his record. He endorsed Luther Strange in the primary for the Alabama Senate seat before he lost Roy Moore. Trump then endorsed Moore who also lost. Trump also endorsed Rick Saccone who lost his special election in Pennsylvania in March.
